data.text: Vaccine update, 36ish hrs post-vaccine: some mild chills and a headache. Axillary lymphadenopathy went away with ibuprofen but now is back. Not bothersome, just kinda weird feeling
@BaeBielle @LingualLoser My opposite side swelled on the first one. Honestly a little nervous about my second dose tomorrow
@LingualLoser Oh very exciting. Your germinal centers were WORKING
@BaeBielle Mine started on the same side then moved to the opposite. Actually hung around for like 4 days
@LingualLoser I’ve heard of several people getting axial lymphadenopathy from the vaccine. Mine is just on the side I received the injection on and is pretty mild (at least for now)
@BaeBielle Omg my armpits hurt so much and no one else said that happened to them. (I felt like crap the day after and slept off feeling like crap the second day)
